  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, siting and appearance, would result in an excessive and obtrusive &lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:&amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px&quot;&gt;feature that would contribute to an unsightly proliferation of signage in the area. Given the established character of the area, the proposed advertisement would have a detimental impact on the quality and appearance of the public realm at the junction between Ridley Road and St Marks Rise. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:&amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px&quot;&gt;As such, the \r\nproposal is considered unacceptable and fails to comply with policies D4\r\n (Delivering good design) and D8 (Public realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies PP1 (Public \r\nRealm), LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) &lt;/span&gt;and LP7 \r\n(Advertisements) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
